    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The thin lens equation assumes a thin lens (thickness much less than focal length) and paraxial rays (close to the optical axis). Real lenses have aberrations. The double-slit formula assumes far-field (Fraunhofer) diffraction, where the screen is far from the slits. Crowell develops near-field (Fresnel) diffraction as well. Our Scheme code computes fringe angles but not the full intensity pattern, which requires summing phasors.</p>

